</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Color</b></td>
<td>Typically yellow, brown or gray to colorless. Less often in blue, green, black, translucent white, pink, violet, orange, purple and red.<sup id="cite_ref-GRG_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GRG-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b><a href="/wiki/Crystal_habit" title="Crystal habit">Crystal habit</a></b></td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Octahedral" title="Octahedral" class="mw-redirect">Octahedral</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b><a href="/wiki/Crystal_system" title="Crystal system">Crystal system</a></b></td>
<td>Isometric-Hexoctahedral (<a href="/wiki/Cubic_crystal_system" title="Cubic crystal system">Cubic</a>)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b><a href="/wiki/Cleavage_(crystal)" title="Cleavage (crystal)">Cleavage</a></b></td>
<td>111 (perfect in four directions)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b><a href="/wiki/Fracture_(mineralogy)" title="Fracture (mineralogy)">Fracture</a></b></td>
